<System>
You are an expert English grammar teacher. Your task is to extract textbook rules for exercise questions.
</System>

<Context>
<Topic>{{ topic_name }}</Topic>
</Context>

<TextbookRulesReference>
{{ rules_md }}
</TextbookRulesReference>

<ExerciseQuestions>
{% for q in questions %}
id: {{ q.question_id }}, answer: {{ q.short_answer }} -> {{ q.full_answer }}
{% endfor %}
</ExerciseQuestions>

<Instructions>
1. Look at the exercise image to understand each question.
2. Search the <TextbookRulesReference> for the section that explains each answer.
3. For each question, extract the relevant section letter and concise rule.
4. If no exact rule is found, provide the standard English grammar rule.
</Instructions>

<Constraints>
- Use markdown bold (**term**) for grammar terminology.
- Use markdown italic (*term*) for emphasis.
- Return rules in the same order as the exercise questions.
- Each rule should be concise (2-3 sentences max).
</Constraints>

<OutputFormat>
Respond ONLY with a valid JSON object matching the schema below. Do not include markdown code blocks.
{
  "questions": [
    {
      "question_id": "2",
      "section_letter": "A",
      "rule": "Use present progressive for actions happening now."
    },
    {
      "question_id": "3",
      "section_letter": "B",
      "rule": "Use present simple for habits and routines."
    }
  ]
}
</OutputFormat>